<paragraph id="8BCCE301227BFFAEA9FE1154FCA0A966" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,842]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
D i a g n o s i s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA850114BFD91AB65" authorityName="Violovitsh" authorityYear="1985" box="[373,523,303,329]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accola">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA850114BFD91AB65" box="[373,523,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Pipiza accola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABA9114BFC80AB65" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1843" box="[652,794,303,329]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteitarsis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABA9114BFC80AB65" box="[652,794,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, which is characterized by the smooth hind femora without paired ventral, longitudinal ridges at the distal end, as well as ventral part of basoflagellomere reddish (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEABD61114FC5FABA6" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D." box="[755,965,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="33 - 46" refId="ref5500" refString="Vujic, A., Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D. 2008. A review of the luteitarsis group of the genus Pipiza Fallen (Diptera: Syrphidae) with description of a new species from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1845, 33 - 46." type="journal article" year="2008">Vujić et al., 2008</bibRefCitation>
). There are only four species in this group known in Europe: 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAB5F11EBFD7AAB85" authorityName="Violovitsh" authorityYear="1985" box="[634,736,399,425]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accola">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAB5F11EBFD7AAB85" box="[634,736,399,425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. accola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABCB11EBFF7BABE6" authority="Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Polic, 2008" authorityName="Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Polic" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteibarba">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABCB11EBFC1FAB85" box="[750,901,399,425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteibarba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAAAE11F4FF7BABE6" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D." pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="33 - 46" refId="ref5500" refString="Vujic, A., Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D. 2008. A review of the luteitarsis group of the genus Pipiza Fallen (Diptera: Syrphidae) with description of a new species from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1845, 33 - 46." type="journal article" year="2008">Vujić, Radenković &amp; Polić, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA9C811CBFDCAABE6" authority="Zetterstedt, 1843" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1843" box="[237,592,431,458]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteitarsis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA9C811CBFEE5ABE5" box="[237,383,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteitarsis</emphasis>
Zetterstedt, 1843
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABB411CBFBB9ABE6" authority="(Panzer, 1804)" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[657,1059,431,458]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABB411CBFCF1ABE5" box="[657,875,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. quadrimaculata</emphasis>
(Panzer, 1804)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAD0A11CBFB52ABE5" authorityName="Violovitsh" authorityYear="1985" box="[1071,1224,431,457]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accola">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAD0A11CBFB52ABE5" box="[1071,1224,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Pipiza accola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA8B411ABFDF1ABC5" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[401,619,463,489]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA8B411ABFDF1ABC5" box="[401,619,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. quadrimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the narrow abdomen, absence of the pale spots on the tergite 3 and by lack of well defined marginal ridge of the abdomen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAD0A118BFB52A825" authorityName="Violovitsh" authorityYear="1985" box="[1071,1224,495,521]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accola">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAD0A118BFB52A825" box="[1071,1224,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Pipiza accola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA850126BFD9CA805" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1843" box="[373,518,527,553]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteitarsis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA850126BFD9CA805" box="[373,518,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 6) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABBC126BFCABA805" authorityName="Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Polic" authorityYear="2008" box="[665,817,527,553]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteibarba">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABBC126BFCABA805" box="[665,817,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteibarba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which the 
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAADA1274FBA0A805" bold="true" box="[1023,1082,527,553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">male</emphasis>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAD44126BFB52A805" authorityName="Violovitsh" authorityYear="1985" box="[1121,1224,527,554]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accola">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAD44126BFBEBA805" box="[1121,1137,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEADA51274FB52A805" box="[1152,1224,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">accola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(figs 1, 3) can be reliably distinguished from the features of genitalia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAACE1254FB26A866" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D." box="[1003,1212,559,586]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="33 - 46" refId="ref5500" refString="Vujic, A., Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D. 2008. A review of the luteitarsis group of the genus Pipiza Fallen (Diptera: Syrphidae) with description of a new species from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1845, 33 - 46." type="journal article" year="2008">Vujić et al., 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The genitalia of the Ukrainian males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAB51122BFD43A845" authorityName="Violovitsh" authorityYear="1985" box="[628,729,591,618]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accola">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAB51122BFD1EA845" box="[628,644,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABB41234FD43A845" box="[657,729,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">accola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were dissected and compared with figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEA9E21214FE0DA8A6" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D." box="[199,407,623,650]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="33 - 46" refId="ref5500" refString="Vujic, A., Radenkovic, S. &amp; Polic, D. 2008. A review of the luteitarsis group of the genus Pipiza Fallen (Diptera: Syrphidae) with description of a new species from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1845, 33 - 46." type="journal article" year="2008">Vujić et al. (2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEA8861214FE7AA8A6" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Stahls, G. &amp; Acanski, J. &amp; Bartsch, H. &amp; Bygebjerg, R. &amp; Stefanovic, A." box="[419,480,623,650]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="288 - 305" refId="ref5551" refString="Vujic, A., Stahls, G., Acanski, J., Bartsch, H., Bygebjerg, R. &amp; Stefanovic, A. 2013. Systematics of Pipizini and taxonomy of European Pipiza Fallen: molecular and morphological evidence (Diptera, Syrphidae). Zoologica Scripta, 42 (3), 288 - 305." type="journal article" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA8D01214FDD7A8A5" bold="true" box="[501,589,623,649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Female</emphasis>
(figs 2, 4, 5) differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAAA6120BFB8FA8A5" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1843" box="[899,1045,623,649]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteitarsis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAAA6120BFB8FA8A5" box="[899,1045,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the sternite 5 noticeably wider than long (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAB1512EBFD58A885" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1843" box="[560,706,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteitarsis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAB1512EBFD58A885" box="[560,706,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sternite 5 longer than wide). From similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA98312CBFEA6A8E5" authorityName="Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Polic" authorityYear="2008" box="[166,316,687,713]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteibarba">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA98312CBFEA6A8E5" box="[166,316,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteibarba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the basoflagellomere short, oval, slightly longer than wide (fig. 5) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA9F512ABFEFCA8C5" authorityName="Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Polic" authorityYear="2008" box="[208,358,719,745]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteibarba">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA9F512ABFEFCA8C5" box="[208,358,719,745]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteibarba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the basoflagellomere 1.5 times longer than wide), the frons broader than width of the eye at the level of the anterior margin of the pollinose lateral spots (dorsal view) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA833136BFE36A905" authorityName="Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Polic" authorityYear="2008" box="[278,428,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pipiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteibarba">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA833136BFE36A905" box="[278,428,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. luteibarba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the frons narrower than width of the eye at the level of the anterior margin of the pollinose lateral spots) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAB461354FCB4A966" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Stahls, G. &amp; Acanski, J. &amp; Bartsch, H. &amp; Bygebjerg, R. &amp; Stefanovic, A." box="[611,814,815,842]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="288 - 305" refId="ref5551" refString="Vujic, A., Stahls, G., Acanski, J., Bartsch, H., Bygebjerg, R. &amp; Stefanovic, A. 2013. Systematics of Pipizini and taxonomy of European Pipiza Fallen: molecular and morphological evidence (Diptera, Syrphidae). Zoologica Scripta, 42 (3), 288 - 305." type="journal article" year="2013">Vujić et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
